Resetting Custom Settings


Reset selected custom settings banks.


1Select I.Q. IMAGE QUALITY SETTING > EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING in the shooting menu and press MENU/OK. assumes that you wish reset movie settings, navigate to □ the movie menus and select EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING.
This to reset settings 2 Highlight the desired custom set- tings bank and press MENU/OK.for still photography. To MOVIE SETTING in EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING AF MF C1 CUSTOM 1 · C2 CUSTOM 2 々 CUSTOM 3 C3 C4 CUSTOM 4 C5 CUSTOM 5 M C6 CUSTOM 6 [BACK] EXIT
3 Highlight RESET CUSTOM SETTING and press MENU/OK. A confirmation dialog will be displayed.I.Q. C1 CUSTOM 1 SAVE CURRENT SETTINGS EDIT/CHECK SAVE THE CHANGES RESET THE CHANGES COPY RESET CUSTOM SETTING EDIT CUSTOM NAME BACK EXIT
4 Highlight OK and press MENU/OK. The selected bank will be reset.RESET CUSTOM SETTING C1 CUSTOM 1 RESET CUSTOM SETTING OK? RESET ALL SETTINGS TO DEFAULT OK CANCEL

| 1 | Select I.Q. IMAGE QUALITY SETTING > EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING in the shooting menu and press MENU/OK. assumes that you wish reset movie settings, navigate to □ the movie menus and select EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING. |

| This to reset settings 2 Highlight the desired custom set- tings bank and press MENU/OK. | for still photography. To MOVIE SETTING in EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING AF MF C1 CUSTOM 1 · C2 CUSTOM 2 々 CUSTOM 3 C3 C4 CUSTOM 4 C5 CUSTOM 5 M C6 CUSTOM 6 [BACK] EXIT |
| 3 Highlight RESET CUSTOM SETTING and press MENU/OK. A confirmation dialog will be displayed. | I.Q. C1 CUSTOM 1 SAVE CURRENT SETTINGS EDIT/CHECK SAVE THE CHANGES RESET THE CHANGES COPY RESET CUSTOM SETTING EDIT CUSTOM NAME BACK EXIT |
| 4 Highlight OK and press MENU/OK. The selected bank will be reset. | RESET CUSTOM SETTING C1 CUSTOM 1 RESET CUSTOM SETTING OK? RESET ALL SETTINGS TO DEFAULT OK CANCEL |
